# "Full Send" Deployment Checklist

When the user says **"full send"**, **"fully deploy"**, or **"deploy everything"**, execute ALL of the following steps in order. Nothing is done until all steps are complete.

## Steps

1. **Bump version** in `create-dmg.sh` — update both `CFBundleVersion` and `CFBundleShortVersionString` to the next version number.
   - This is **not dynamic**. The DMG bundle metadata comes from the hardcoded `Info.plist` block inside `create-dmg.sh`.

2. **Commit** all changes:
   ```
   git add <changed files>
   git commit -m "vX.Y: <summary of changes>"
   ```

3. **Create GitHub release BEFORE pushing** (so CI can upload the DMG to it):
   ```
   gh release create vX.Y \
     --title "vX.Y — <title>" \
     --notes "<release notes>"
   ```

4. **Push to main** — triggers CI (`.github/workflows/release.yml`) which:
   - Builds the Release binary via `xcodebuild`
   - Runs `create-dmg.sh` to package the `.app`
   - Uploads `DICTATR.dmg` to the new GitHub release
   ```
   git push
   ```

5. **Website updates automatically**:
   - The download URL is stable: `releases/latest/download/DICTATR.dmg`
   - The visible website version label is now dynamic and is fetched from the latest GitHub release `tag_name`
   - No manual website version bump is needed unless the page copy/layout itself changes

6. **Swap the locally running app** (run in parallel with CI):
   ```bash
   # Build
   DEVELOPER_DIR=/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer xcodebuild \
     -scheme DICTATR -configuration Release -destination 'platform=macOS' build

   # Find binary
   BINARY=$(find ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData -path "*/Release/DICTATR" -type f | head -1)

   # Kill, replace, relaunch
   kill $(pgrep -x DICTATR)
   cp "$BINARY" /Applications/DICTATR.app/Contents/MacOS/DICTATR

   # Keep local Finder/About version metadata in sync with the deployed binary
   /usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c "Set :CFBundleVersion X.Y" /Applications/DICTATR.app/Contents/Info.plist
   /usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c "Set :CFBundleShortVersionString X.Y" /Applications/DICTATR.app/Contents/Info.plist

   open /Applications/DICTATR.app
   ```

7. **Verify versions after deploy**:
   - `gh release view vX.Y` should show the uploaded `DICTATR.dmg`
   - `/Applications/DICTATR.app/Contents/Info.plist` should report the same version as the release
   - `docs/index.html` should show the latest release version automatically once GitHub Pages redeploys

